  <description><![CDATA[<p>The luxurious Belmond Hotel Caruso is perched high on the clifftops of Ravello, affording it some of the most spectacular views on the <a data-udi="umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47}" title="Amalfi Coast">Amalfi Coast</a>.</p>
<p>This five-star retreat makes the most of its stunning location, with a heated infinity pool gazing over the cliff edge onto the glistening Mediterranean waters 1,000 feet below. Comfortable sun loungers are placed around the pool to create a relaxing space for those that want to just sit back and enjoy the sun. The hotel’s century-old gardens lead away from the pool and wind around the hotel’s stunning façade, offering glimpses of the panoramic views.</p>
<p>The hotel originates back to the 11th century and was originally built as a palazzo by the D’Afflitto family of Rome. The Belmond Group have carefully restored the property to its original grandeur and have created a truly romantic and elegant retreat. The fine dining Belvedere Restaurant boasts a sea view terrace and serves incredible dishes using locally-sourced ingredients. The Arcade Bar provides a welcoming spot to enjoy an expertly-made pre-dinner cocktail in a sophisticated space with frescoed ceilings. Guest rooms have been well-furnished too in a classic Italian style. Each is unique and boasts sumptuous furnishings and modern comforts.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 10 mins by private car from Naples Airport</p>]]></description>
